body_html: The tf.contrib.data API in TF 1.2 doesn't support dictionaries as Dataset nested structures. This feature was added in TF 1.3. To work around it, you will need to convert the dictionary to a tuple or namedtuple.
body_text: The tf.contrib.data API in TF 1.2 doesn't support dictionaries as Dataset nested structures. This feature was added in TF 1.3. To work around it, you will need to convert the dictionary to a tuple or namedtuple.
body: The `tf.contrib.data` API in TF 1.2 doesn't support dictionaries as `Dataset` nested structures. This feature was added in TF 1.3. To work around it, you will need to convert the dictionary to a `tuple` or `namedtuple`.
